<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-424-011  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 424 011.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  July 3 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Computer Communications wins data communications contract.andO;(Oklahoma Department of Public Safety awards contract)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Endrijonas, Janet.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Computer Communications Inc. (contracts).andO;Ticker:    CCMM.andO;Topic:     ContractsOklahoma. Department of Public SafetyData CommunicationsLaw enforcementTelecommunications.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>COMPUTER COMMUNICATIONS WINS DATA COMMUNICATIONS CONTRACT TORRANCE,CALIFORNIA, U.S.A., 1990 JUN 29 (NB) -- Computer Communications has beenawarded a contract from the Oklahoma Department of Public Safety for a lawenforcement data communications system.andP;  The contract was awarded on anindustry competitive bid.andM;Under the terms of the contract, Computer Communications will provide amessage switching system using the company's Data Express communicationsprocessors.andP;  The system is to be delivered early in 1991.andM;The system will be installed for the Oklahoma Law EnforcementTelecommunications System and will allow law enforcement and criminal justicepersonnel to exchange information throughout the state and with other states.andO;The system will provide direct communications with the FBI's National CrimeInformation Center and National Law Enforcement Telecommunications System andwill service the Commercial Drivers License Information System.andM;The System to be developed by Computer Communications will communicatethrough a wide variety of terminals and protocols handling up to 90,000messages per hour.andP;  The system will include a database management system witha 4th generation language for applications development.andP;  The message handlingsystem will be compatible with the CCITT X.400 international standard.andM;(Janet Endrijonas/19900629/Press Contact: Ervin K. Dorff, ComputerCommunications, 800-421-1178)</TEXT><